    {
      "id": "fcb365569fce0d9f123f7ece93fa2da9edbf810a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 597,
        "name": "Sebastien Buisson",
        "email": "sbuisson@ddn.com",
        "username": "sbuisson"
      },
      "date": "2019-04-15 16:02:51.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\n(1 comment)\n\nHave you looked at the implementation of enc_pools in lustre/ptlrpc/sec_bulk.c? Allocating contiguous pages is very much like what enc_pools are made for. Maybe the code for enc_pools should be moved (and renamed?) so that it can be used for compression, but we may try to avoid duplicating what is already available.\n\nAlso, is this code CPT aware?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "e9a376bdffd5b735b4719ada48bbb634be82574f",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2019-04-15 19:44:47.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nI like to add the kernel has a implementation called zbud which is very much like this work.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "6447875395532a026d520213756d247e6ba5393f",
